title: Check your tickets! Winner of $50m jackpot STILL doesn't know they are a millionaire
text:
Numbers were 5, 32, 22, 13, 20, 25 and 42, supplementary numbers 21 and 23

Unregistered players urged to check tickets as Oz Lotto officials can't call them

One lucky Australian is the nation's newest multi-millionaire after winning Tuesday's Oz Lotto jackpot, but they still haven't claimed their prize.

The mystery winner held the only division one winning entry in Oz Lotto draw 1339 and takes home the entire $50 million prize.

While the search for the lucky ticket holder continues the vendor where it was purchased has been revealed as Leumeah Newsagency in Sydney's south-west.

As the Leumeah entry was not registered to a player card, officials have no way to contact the ticketholder.

One lucky Australian is the nation's newest multi-millionaire after winning Tuesday's Oz Lotto jackpot, but they still haven't claimed their prize (stock image)

Leumeah Newsagency owner Ben Van Cao said he was ecstatic to have sold the winning ticket.

'Wow! That is very good news! Very, very good news!' he said.

'We are so excited. We've sold two division one winning entries in the past but nothing ever this big.

'We hope we can unite the winner with their prize soon!'

The Lott spokesperson Bronwyn Spencer is urging everyone who purchased an entry at Leumeah Newsagency to check their tickets.

She also reminded everyone to register their tickets to player cards.

While the search for the lucky ticket holder continues the vendor where it was purchased has been revealed as Leumeah Newsagency in Sydney's south-west (pictured)

'We recommend all players register their entries to our free membership service to ensure their prizes are secure and they can be contacted directly with the good news of a big win,' she said.

The winning numbers were 5, 32, 22, 13, 20, 25 and 42.

The supplementary numbers were 21 and 23.

This is the tenth division one winning entry in Oz Lotto so far this year.

Tuesday's night division one winner became the tenth Oz Lotto winner who have shared in $285 million won so far this year.

Three were from Victoria and NSW while Queensland had two.
description: One lucky Australian is the nation's newest multi-millionaire after winning Tuesday's Oz Lotto jackpot, but they still haven't claimed their prize.
authors: Charlotte Karp For Daily Mail Australia
